	<text xml:lang="la">
		<body>
			<div>
				<p>
					<s n="1" xml:lang="la">Nuper unas ex <placeName ref="l830">Anglia</placeName> literas recepi datas ad dominum <persName ref="p1283">Gesnerum</persName>, quas ut tradas rogo.</s>
					<s n="2" xml:lang="la">Bellum inter <placeName ref="l830">Angliam</placeName> et <placeName ref="l832">Galliam</placeName> gliscit; nam <persName ref="p8375">Anglię</persName> regina <placeName ref="l2524">Scotos</placeName> vicinos et coniunctos propter religionem susceptam a <placeName ref="l832">Gallo</placeName> oppugnatos indefensos relinquere non vult.</s>
					<s n="3" xml:lang="la">Nam sub prętextu religionis bellum ceptum a <placeName ref="l832">Gallo</placeName> in totius insulę suppressionem directum est.</s>
					<s n="4" xml:lang="la"><placeName ref="l875">Hispaniarum</placeName> quoque rex sub hiis spetiosis titulis, nempe hęreseos et rebellionis in armorum societatem adducitur immemor antiquissimorum fęderum et sępius acceptorum benefitiorum a priscis et nostri ęvi <persName ref="p8375">Anglię</persName> regibus.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="5" xml:lang="la"><placeName ref="l822">Germanos</placeName> veros et memores sui officii spes est non militaturos in hoc nefando bello <placeName ref="l832">Gallo</placeName>.</s>
					<s n="6" xml:lang="la">Si <placeName ref="l862">Helvetii</placeName> quoque detrectarent impia arma induere et gladios in innoxios stringere, nihil regem pręclari perfecturum verismile esset.</s>
					<s n="7" xml:lang="la">Regina et terra et mari suas copias admovit ad <placeName ref="l2524">Scotiam</placeName>, et nisi <placeName ref="l832">Gallię</placeName> rex ęquissimas conditiones et accipiat et det, regina Scotię libertatem armis asserere annitetur.</s>
					<s n="8" xml:lang="la">De reginę connubio nihildum accepi; maior natu <placeName>Suetię</placeName> regis in <placeName ref="l830">Angliam</placeName> adventurus dicitur.</s>
					<s n="9" xml:lang="la">Orator Cesaris ibidem quoque hęret; verum an exorator [fu]turus sit, plęrique dubitant.</s>
					<s n="10" xml:lang="la">Fertur reginam inter horrida <persName>Martis</persName> arma tristes hymenęos facere nolle, ne liberatori magis necessitate coacta nupsisse quam delecto coniugi dicatur.</s>
					<s n="11" xml:lang="la">Religio in <placeName ref="l830">Anglia</placeName> fęlices successus habet, qui ut quotidie magis fęlices sint, deus implorandus est.</s>
					<s n="12" xml:lang="la">Quęso, ut me commendes d. <persName ref="p8111">Martyri</persName>.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="13" xml:lang="la">Bene valeas.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="14" xml:lang="la"><placeName ref="l491">Argentinę</placeName>.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<note type="address">[Adresse fehlt.]</note>
				</p>
				<p>
					<note>[Fragment von <persName ref="p8121">Monts</persName> Hand.]</note>
					<note>[Datum: Vgl.: <persName ref="p8121">Mont</persName> an <persName ref="p495">HB</persName>, 20. Feb. und 13. Juli 1560. <persName ref="p495">HB</persName> an <persName ref="p8009">Fabricius</persName> 12. und 19. Juli 1560.]</note>
				</p>
			</div>
